&lt;p&gt;Translation [[Ogihara 2009]]: 261:&lt;br&gt;
a1 /// should enter. It should be learned in this way. ///&lt;br&gt;
a2 /// 1 One should not enter (into the house) while much looking up.&lt;br&gt;
a3 2 One (should not sit in the house) while much looking up.&lt;br&gt;
a4 3 One should enter into the house&lt;br&gt;
a5 with little sound. 4 One (should sit) in the house with little sound. (5)&lt;br&gt;
a6 /// One should enter into the house ///&lt;br&gt;
a7 /// One should not (enter) into the house in squatting position (8)&lt;br&gt;
b1 One should not sit in the house in squatting position. (9) One should (not) enter into the house&lt;br&gt;
b2 (while having covered the head). 10 One should not (sit in the house) while having covered the head. 11&lt;br&gt;
b3 One should (not) enter into the house having done ... over the head. ///&lt;br&gt;
b4 /// One should (not) sit in the house having done ... over the head. ///&lt;br&gt;
b5 /// One should not enter into the house having turned by the shoulder. (15)&lt;br&gt;
b6 One should not sit in the house having turned by the shoulder. 16 One should&lt;br&gt;
b7 not enter into the house having supported the side. 17
